a Bragg reflection principle. b Helical superstructure of CLC molecules. c Selective reflection of Ch-LCs. d Construction of helical gradients with polymer networks to broaden the reflection bands. e Schematic of the method of breaking the reflection limit. Reproduced with permission from ref. 127. Copyright 2009, American Chemical Society

